name: KB5 The Hardcore issue
description:
Feeling as good as it looks, the Hardcore issue was launched in June 2011 to rave reviews including this from Germaine Greer 'well at least it's not completely full of words...'
 The Hardcore contains sex, drugs and swear words.

name: KB4 Smoke & Mirrors
description:
Issue 4 of KnockBack magazine - The shiny one

Released in 2010, this issue features words by some of the UK's finest female minds. Guaranteed to make you laugh out loud at least once and useful at festivals if you've forgotten your compact.


(All orders include postage)

name: KB3 The Well Dressed issue
description:
The one with killer heels

Released before we realised we love expensive covers, this issue is vaguely threads themed

name: Three for a tenner
description:
Get the last three remaining issues for a tenner, which is an actual bargain. We stick a badge in there too. 

Double points.

name: KB complete *SOLD OUT*
description:
Unfortunately for collectors of sets, we are no longer able to supply a complete and functioning back catalogue. 

Issue 1 has finally bitten the dust, the last box was ceremoniously crushed underfoot and put out with the recycling.  Don't worry though you can download the pdf for free here:
http://www.knockback.co.uk/back-issues.php#

Issue 2 - Sugar coated and sold out, this issue was released in 2007 and is choc-full of typos, grammar upsets and inappropriate references to cake. Due to popular demand we have not made this available as a pdf. 

Issues 3, 4 and 5 are still in stock although increasingly in short supply so that's something to be cheery about.
